1
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:01,200
welcome back

2
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:04,066
last time we made the whole plat-line

3
00:00:04,066 --> 00:00:05,733
now we have enough iridium

4
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:09,266
for both the HSS-S coils and IV energy hatches

5
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:11,533
we still miss some indium

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,933
but we can easily get it

7
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:16,300
by dissolving a lot of minerals in sulfuric acid

8
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,333
and then destroying all of our aluminum

9
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:21,000
to extract indium from that slurry

10
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,733
this simple but expensive process

11
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:26,533
can be made by just two multi blocks

12
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:30,000
and once we get all the required ingredients

13
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,466
we can start producing indium slurry

14
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,733
which will self-feedback into the chemical reactor

15
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,466
to extract the indium

16
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,266
and with that

17
00:00:39,266 --> 00:00:42,333
we can finally have the IV energy hatches

18
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:45,000
and with that we can now melt arcanite

19
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,633
and thus craft the large processing factory

20
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:51,400
this machine has three working modes

21
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:55,100
and we are going to make one multi block for each working mode

22
00:00:55,266 --> 00:00:56,600
the first one we will want

23
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,033
is one in miscellaneous mode

24
00:00:58,033 --> 00:01:00,033
to use as a laser engraver

25
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:03,100
it can do its job even outside of a clean room

26
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,066
and to upgrade it

27
00:01:04,066 --> 00:01:06,800
we only have to swap the energy hatches

28
00:01:07,466 --> 00:01:08,600
the next one we want

29
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:10,700
will still be in miscellaneous mode

30
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:12,400
but this time

31
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,800
by changing the circuits

32
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:17,100
it will work in autoclave and fluid solidifier mode

33
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,100
wall shared

34
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:21,400
we have the next one in metal mode

35
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:25,600
which will do as a lathe, compressor and magnetic polarizer

36
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,000
next

37
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,900
we shall have one machine dedicated to solidifying fluids

38
00:01:31,066 --> 00:01:34,833
this will use some special and expensive input hatches

39
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,866
to not mix up the molds

40
00:01:37,866 --> 00:01:40,200
now that we can easily work fluids

41
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,833
we can work on the next upgrade

42
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:43,600
volcanoes

43
00:01:43,666 --> 00:01:46,533
however we still miss two ingredients

44
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:49,200
yttrium and ZPM circuits

45
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:50,900
to get the yttrium

46
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,300
we can process rare earth in a chemical bath

47
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,233
with some acids

48
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:55,733
and then dehydrate it

49
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,700
this will also yield a lot of other stuff too

50
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,266
meanwhile

51
00:02:00,266 --> 00:02:03,200
the only option we can use for the ZPM circuit

52
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,466
is the quantum processor mainframe

53
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,933
thus we quickly make all the patterns

54
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:09,833
to craft these circuits

55
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,933
and with that

56
00:02:10,933 --> 00:02:13,466
we can now craft our first volcano

57
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:16,400
and while we wait for it to be crafted

58
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,066
we can go farm some withers

59
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:20,800
and once the crafting is done

60
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:24,033
we can promote our EBFs to volcanoes

61
00:02:25,066 --> 00:02:27,600
those have many bonuses that EBFs don't have

62
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,533
and the only downside is that

63
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:31,500
they eat some blazing pyrotheum

64
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,533
we could passively craft it

65
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:36,800
but to have a better look on the amount

66
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,700
we shall have a level maintainer to auto-craft it

67
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,333
this level maintainer will keep issuing crafting orders

68
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:47,100
to ensure we always have some stocked up

69
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:52,633
and we shall also stock up some other of the most commonly used materials

70
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:55,700
the main advantage of the volcanoes

71
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:58,200
is that they can do parallel melting

72
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:58,933
however

73
00:02:58,933 --> 00:03:02,633
some materials such as iridium require a lot of power

74
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:06,100
thus making us unable to make more than one at a time

75
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,866
but we are still using two EV energy hatches

76
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:13,400
so time to upgrade to two IV ones

77
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:17,666
and we are going to need two for each of the four volcanoes

78
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:22,600
but that totals to a potential consumption of 16 IV amps

79
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,900
which is the whole power that our current base can handle

80
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:30,766
and since we will also want to run the other machines we have

81
00:03:30,766 --> 00:03:33,600
it is time to move to a multi block battery

82
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,800
to manage our main power node

83
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,600
we are doing a lapotronic super capacitor

84
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,900
with nine IV capacitors

85
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:44,266
once we crafted all the parts

86
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,100
we can assemble it in a corner of our main building

87
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:48,400
and then

88
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:52,066
we will find out that this thing has no power sockets

89
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:56,866
so we quickly craft some 16 amps IV ones

90
00:03:57,933 --> 00:04:00,866
and also we will need some input plugs

91
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:02,900
once everything is done

92
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:04,333
we can finish the assembly

93
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:07,466
and rewire our main power cables to the new battery

94
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:12,200
since we can't easily see how much power is flowing

95
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:14,400
we shall use a Gregtech sensor kit

96
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,633
and an industrial information panel

97
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:19,200
to have a clear view of how our power is doing

98
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,600
from the main hall of our base

99
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,100
and it was then that we realized that

100
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:29,200
being able to manage more than 16 amps of current was not enough

101
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,800
we also have to produce such amounts of power

102
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:35,033
and the best way to do so

103
00:04:35,033 --> 00:04:37,700
is probably by using the charge we have left

104
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,233
to craft a bunch of nuclear reactors

105
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,500
this time we are going to use a fluid setup

106
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,200
in a dedicated building

107
00:04:47,933 --> 00:04:50,900
as you can already see from this quick overview

108
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:56,333
this system is going to be slightly more complex than the ones we have seen so far

109
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,466
the two tanks on top

110
00:04:58,466 --> 00:05:02,033
are for the coolant which is heated up by the reactors

111
00:05:02,866 --> 00:05:05,600
the third tank is for the distilled water

112
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:08,433
and it has a sensor to shut off the heat exchangers

113
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,633
if it runs low

114
00:05:11,866 --> 00:05:14,333
we collect all the steam from the four machines

115
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:16,200
in a single giant hatch

116
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,633
where we move it using the only pipe with enough capacity

117
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,533
ae2 peer to peer

118
00:05:23,033 --> 00:05:25,633
and we move it to a couple of turbines

119
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:27,866
which we will be running in loose mode

120
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,233
after turning it on

121
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:32,266
this system will require some time

122
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:34,033
to reach peak efficiency

123
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,733
and also to speed up the turbines

124
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:40,233
now those turbines can handle at maximum

125
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:43,933
32700 EU per tick before blowing up

126
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:45,600
so we must be careful at

127
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:48,066
how much steam we run through them

128
00:05:48,066 --> 00:05:49,500
using a regulator

129
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:53,100
we can precisely fine tune how much the flow shall be

130
00:05:53,866 --> 00:05:56,933
and once we finished fine tuning the turbines

131
00:05:56,933 --> 00:05:59,666
we realize we have some leftover steam

132
00:06:00,466 --> 00:06:03,300
since that would mean losing water from the loop

133
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,933
we will also want to fine tune

134
00:06:04,933 --> 00:06:08,266
how much coolant is moved through the heat exchangers

135
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:10,633
once again

136
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:13,200
instead of using a spreadsheet and some math

137
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:16,200
we slowly fine tune the values by trial and error

138
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,800
because that's more fun

139
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:19,200
and we do that

140
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:23,966
until we find the point where the production and consumption are perfectly balanced

141
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:25,733
and the system stabilizes

142
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,600
now we can go back and see that

143
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:32,066
our batteries are charging up quite fast

144
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:35,066
since we can't easily turn off the fluid system

145
00:06:35,066 --> 00:06:37,666
we are instead toggling the vacuum reactors

146
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:40,200
when the batteries are at half the capacity

147
00:06:42,066 --> 00:06:42,633
and with that

148
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:46,233
I think it is time to look on what's the next objective

149
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:50,733
and the only thing preventing us from entering the next tier

150
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:52,433
is an assembly line

151
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:57,633
crafting one requires a lot of materials

152
00:06:57,633 --> 00:06:59,233
but we are good on about everything

153
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:01,800
except for blaze rods and platinum

154
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,366
to get Blaze Rod

155
00:07:04,366 --> 00:07:06,700
we can do an industrial mob farm

156
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,266
meanwhile for the platinum

157
00:07:10,266 --> 00:07:13,000
we are currently gathering it as a byproduct

158
00:07:14,066 --> 00:07:14,533
however

159
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:17,600
a better way is to go visit some new planets

160
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,066
where it spawns as a more rich ore

161
00:07:20,866 --> 00:07:23,066
since it can be found on tier 3 planets

162
00:07:23,066 --> 00:07:25,866
and we will soon have to go there anyways

163
00:07:25,866 --> 00:07:27,700
we might as well craft a rocket now

164
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:29,233
and get platinum there

165
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:30,633
however

166
00:07:30,633 --> 00:07:33,300
after quickly assembling and building the rocket

167
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,800
we find ourselves in a dire spot

168
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,400
we do not have a proper fuel

169
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,400
for such an advanced rocket

170
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:43,500
we will have to synthesize hydrazine in a chemical plant

171
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:47,233
but that's going to be the story of the next episodes

172
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:01,200
欢迎回来！

173
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:04,066
上期我们做了整条铂处理产线

174
00:00:04,066 --> 00:00:05,733
现在我们有足够的铱

175
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:09,266
来做高速钢-S 线圈和 IV 能源仓

176
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:11,533
虽然我们还是缺少了一些铟

177
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,933
但得到它并非难事

178
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:16,300
通过在硫酸中溶解大量闪铅和方锌矿

179
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:18,333
再加上我们的铝粉

180
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:21,000
便可从铟富集溶液获得铟粉

181
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,733
这个简单但昂贵的过程

182
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:26,533
只需两个多方块机器即可完成

183
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:30,000
一旦我们将原料集齐

184
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,466
生产铟浆便指日可待

185
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,733
它会自动输入到化学反应釜中

186
00:00:35,733 --> 00:00:37,466
来提取出铟

187
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,266
有了这个

188
00:00:39,266 --> 00:00:42,333
我们终于可以制作 IV 能源仓了

189
00:00:42,733 --> 00:00:45,000
用来融化奥金锭

190
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,633
从而来制作大型加工厂

191
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:51,400
此机器有三种工作模式

192
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:55,100
我们要为每个工作模式各做一台机器

193
00:00:55,266 --> 00:00:56,600
第一台机器

194
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,033
将运行在杂项模式下

195
00:00:58,033 --> 00:01:00,033
用作激光蚀刻机

196
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:03,100
它可以直接执行超净间配方

197
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,066
如果要升级它

198
00:01:04,066 --> 00:01:06,800
我们只需要升级能源仓

199
00:01:07,466 --> 00:01:08,600
下一台机器

200
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:10,700
仍是杂项模式下的机器

201
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:12,400
但这一次

202
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,800
通过改变电路板

203
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:17,100
它将在高压釜和流体固化器模式下工作

204
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,466
共用结构方块后

205
00:01:19,466 --> 00:01:21,400
我们做了金属模式的九合一

206
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:25,600
这会被用作车床、压缩机、两极磁化仪

207
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,000
下一个

208
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:30,900
我们做一台专用于凝固流体的机器

209
00:01:31,066 --> 00:01:34,833
它要使用特殊且昂贵的输入仓

210
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,866
来避免混淆模具

211
00:01:37,866 --> 00:01:40,200
现在我们可以轻松处理流体了

212
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,833
我们继续下一个升级

213
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:43,600
炽焰高炉

214
00:01:43,666 --> 00:01:46,533
然而，我们仍缺少两种原材料

215
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:49,200
钇和 ZPM 电路板

216
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:50,900
想要获得钇粉

217
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,933
我们需要使用一些硫酸

218
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:54,233
在化学浸洗机中处理稀土

219
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:55,733
然后将其脱水

220
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,700
不过这同时也会产生很多其他材料

221
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,266
与此同时

222
00:02:00,266 --> 00:02:03,200
我们唯一能做的 ZPM 电路板

223
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,466
是量子处理器主机

224
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,933
所以我们迅速写出相应的所有样板

225
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:09,833
来制作这些电路板

226
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,933
有了它

227
00:02:10,933 --> 00:02:13,466
我们可以制作第一台炽焰高炉

228
00:02:13,633 --> 00:02:16,400
在等待它被制作出来的同时

229
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,066
我们去刷一些凋零

230
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:20,800
一旦制作完成

231
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:24,033
我们将工业高炉晋升为炽焰高炉

232
00:02:25,066 --> 00:02:27,600
它有很多工业高炉没有的优点

233
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,533
而唯一的缺点是

234
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:31,500
需要不断消耗烈焰之炽焰

235
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,533
我们可以为此做个被动产线

236
00:02:34,533 --> 00:02:36,800
但为了更好地查看其数量

237
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,700
我们用一台 ME 请求器来自动制作它

238
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,333
这个机器将持续发配配方

239
00:02:44,333 --> 00:02:47,100
以确保库存不会出现空缺

240
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:52,633
我们再维持一些其他常用材料的库存

241
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:55,700
炽焰高炉的主要优势

242
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:58,200
是它可以进行并行处理

243
00:02:58,200 --> 00:02:58,933
然而

244
00:02:58,933 --> 00:03:02,633
一些如铱这类的材料需要巨额能量

245
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:06,100
使得我们无法进行并行

246
00:03:06,666 --> 00:03:09,866
我们仍在使用两个 EV 能源仓

247
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:13,400
是时候升级到 IV 的了

248
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:17,666
四台炽焰高炉各需要 2 个能源仓

249
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:22,600
这意味着 16A IV 的潜在耗电

250
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:26,900
而这是我们基地能承受的全部电力

251
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:30,766
但由于我们也想运行一些其他机器

252
00:03:30,766 --> 00:03:33,600
是时候做超级兰波顿电容库了

253
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:35,800
使用它来作为主要电网

254
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,600
我们将制作一个 LSC

255
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,900
并安装 9 个 IV 兰波顿电容

256
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:44,266
集齐完所有部件

257
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,100
我们就在主楼的角落里进行安装

258
00:03:47,933 --> 00:03:48,400
然后

259
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:52,066
我们发现这东西没有输出能源的地方

260
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:56,866
所以我们快速制作了一些 16A 动力仓

261
00:03:57,933 --> 00:04:00,866
同时能量仓也是必要的

262
00:04:01,233 --> 00:04:02,900
一旦一切完成

263
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:04,333
我们便完成安装

264
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:07,466
并将主电缆接入新电池

265
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:12,200
由于时刻监视电力流动情况很重要

266
00:04:12,233 --> 00:04:14,400
我们将使用 Gregtech 传感器套件

267
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,633
和工业信息面板

268
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:18,866
从基地的大厅

269
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:21,600
来清楚地监视电力情况

270
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,100
此时我们意识到

271
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:29,200
16A 电流是远远不够的

272
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,800
我们必须生产大量电力

273
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:35,033
最好的方法是

274
00:04:35,033 --> 00:04:37,700
利用我们剩下的电量

275
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:40,233
制造一堆核反应堆

276
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,500
这次我们将使用大型热交换机

277
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,200
来使用流体发电

278
00:04:47,933 --> 00:04:50,900
如你所见

279
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:56,333
它比强冷核电复杂得多

280
00:04:57,300 --> 00:04:58,466
上面的两个超级缸

281
00:04:58,466 --> 00:05:02,033
用于装载被反应堆加热的冷却剂

282
00:05:02,866 --> 00:05:05,600
第三个超级缸装蒸馏水

283
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:08,433
它有一个用于关机的传感器

284
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,633
防止超级缸缺水

285
00:05:11,866 --> 00:05:14,333
我们收集四台机器里所有的蒸汽

286
00:05:14,333 --> 00:05:16,200
并储存在一个超级输出仓中

287
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:19,633
我们使用唯一能胜任此任务的管道

288
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,533
AE2 p2p管道

289
00:05:23,033 --> 00:05:25,633
我们将蒸汽输送到几个大型蒸汽高压涡轮中

290
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:27,866
并使用更多流量的节流模式启动

291
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,233
开机后

292
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:32,266
这个机器需要一段时间暖机

293
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:34,033
来达到最高效率

294
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,733
同时也会增加涡轮机的效率

295
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:40,233
这些涡轮机在流量过载爆炸前

296
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:43,933
可以生产出 32,700 EU/t 的电量

297
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:45,600
所以我们必须小心

298
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:48,066
这些机器通入了多少过热蒸汽

299
00:05:48,066 --> 00:05:49,500
通过使用流体校准器

300
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:53,100
我们可以精确调整流量

301
00:05:53,866 --> 00:05:56,933
一旦完成对涡轮的微调

302
00:05:56,933 --> 00:05:59,666
我们意识到有些蒸汽并没有进入循环

303
00:06:00,466 --> 00:06:03,300
这意味着我们将失去不少的水

304
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,933
所以我们也得微调

305
00:06:04,933 --> 00:06:08,266
进入热交换器的冷却剂流量

306
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:10,633
这一次

307
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:13,200
我们还是不用现存表格或手算

308
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:16,200
而是通过手动微调来逼近最优

309
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,800
因为这更有趣

310
00:06:18,533 --> 00:06:19,200
我们一直这么做

311
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:23,966
直到找到输入和输出的平衡点

312
00:06:23,966 --> 00:06:25,733
与之同时系统也将稳定下来

313
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,600
现在我们回去看看

314
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:32,066
发现电池充得很快

315
00:06:32,066 --> 00:06:35,066
既然我们不能轻易关闭流体反应堆

316
00:06:35,066 --> 00:06:37,666
我们将在电容库电量高于一半时

317
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:40,200
关闭强冷核电

318
00:06:42,066 --> 00:06:42,633
有了这个

319
00:06:42,633 --> 00:06:46,233
是时候推进度了

320
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:50,733
唯一阻止我们进入下一电压的是

321
00:06:50,733 --> 00:06:52,433
装配线

322
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:57,633
制作一台装配线需要大量的原材料

323
00:06:57,633 --> 00:06:59,233
但我们库存良好

324
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:01,800
除了烈焰棒和铂粉

325
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,400
为了获取烈焰棒

326
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,700
我们制作一个工业屠宰场

327
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,266
而铂粉方面

328
00:07:10,266 --> 00:07:13,000
我们目前正以副产品来收集它

329
00:07:14,066 --> 00:07:14,533
然而

330
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:17,600
更好的解决方法是去往一些新的行星

331
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,066
在那里将不再是生成贫瘠矿

332
00:07:20,866 --> 00:07:23,066
由于 T3 行星将会生成铂矿

333
00:07:23,066 --> 00:07:25,866
而且我们总是要去 T3 星球的

334
00:07:25,866 --> 00:07:27,700
不如现在就造个火箭

335
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:29,233
并在那里获得铂金属粉

336
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:30,633
然而

337
00:07:30,633 --> 00:07:33,300
在快速组装和建造火箭后

338
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,800
我们发现自己身处尴尬境地

339
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,400
我们并没有合适的燃料

340
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:39,400
来供给如此先进的火箭

341
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:43,500
我们得在化工厂里合成密集肼

342
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:47,233
而这将是下一集的故事了

343
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,933
（此为土法制铟）

344
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,633
（原作者玩的是测试版，正式版已废弃九合一）

345
00:01:31,066 --> 00:01:34,833
（固化仓）

346
00:03:30,766 --> 00:03:33,600
（Lapotronic SuperCapacitor简称LSC）

347
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:50,733
（剧差压, Ludicrous Voltage, LuV）

